            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Collection of mainly 19th and 20th century advertising ephemera. Formats in the collection include American trade cards, lottery tickets, handbills, labels, broadsides, calendars, billheads, price lists, advertising fans, and other materials of history and popular culture.Media range from rough woodcuts to chromolithographs.</abstract>
        </did>
        <custodhist id="ref4">
            <head>Provenance</head>
            <p>Gift of Bella C. Landauer between 1926 and 1960, with later additions by her son, James D. Landauer. Other advertising ephemera by a variety of donors, as well as material with no attributed provenance, were added to the collection after Landauer's death.</p>
        </custodhist>
